    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"different\" thing feels like a lie people tell to be nice. It doesn't feel like individuality, it feels like a malfunction. Like, if a machine has a core processing error that makes the whole system unstable, you don't just call it \"unique\"—you recognize it's a failure. If the error is foundational to the biology, isn't it just a wasted process?",
