    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"accepting it\" is just another way of saying \"enduring a malfunction.\" if the system is inherently unstable and the errors are hardwired, then the adaptation is just a way to keep a broken process running for no reason. from a purely technical standpoint, if a system can't achieve its intended function because of a fatal error, isn't the only logical solution to just stop the process? to prevent further errors from occurring?",
